  "text": "Tests for the effect of transposase on the ring-X P element: Figure 2 shows the experimental (e) and control crosses (c) used to monitor the effect of P[D2-3](99B) on the ring-X chromosome. F 1 test males (asterisk) were produced by crossing males from the RCa1 and RCa2 stocks to attached-X females homozygous for the P[D2-3](99B) transposon (e) and lacking the transposon (c). Single F 1 males from both crosses were then crossed to either attached-X females or normal females. The cross to attached-X females ensures that the F 2 progeny containing the ring-X appear in hemizygous condition in male offspring, while the cross to normal females results in ring-X progeny in heterozygous state in female offspring. Half the (e) progeny are expected to carry the P[D2-3](99B) transposon. Not all ring-X progeny are expected to carry the P[CaSpeR](17C), as the excision rate in the parents is of the order of 20-30% [CITATION_1] .",
